s=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uni1718715029734.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uni1718715029734.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uni1718715029734.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vfn1665702600415\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n $formmod (deprecated)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vfn1665702600415___formmoddeprecated__267007\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the modification status of data in the current Form component.\n </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__note_w2313ab1b7b3_w2314ab1b7_w2315ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span>\n         function is deprecated. It has been superseded by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancemod</span>, which is\n         applicable to all component types. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"atw1665702600492.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/atw1665702600492.html\" title=\"Return or set the modification status of data in the current component instance.\">$instancemod</a>. </div>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__topic_d83960e1_d83961e1_d83962e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__p_d83963e1_d83964e1_d83965e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Expression</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__p_d83966e1_d83967e1_d83968e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">set</span> | <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reset</span>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__topic_d55552e1_d55553e1_d55554e1_d55555e1_d55556e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1184410e100\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1__entry__1\">\n 0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1__entry__2\">\n In the following cases:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__li_d34379e1_d34380e1_d34381e1\">No field has been modified\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__li_d34382e1_d34383e1_d34384e1\">No occurrences have been added or removed\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__li_d34385e1_d34386e1_d34387e1\">No entities are painted on the form\n </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1__entry__1\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vfn1665702600415__table_d8687e1_d8688e1_d8689e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">In the following cases:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__li_d34388e1_d34389e1_d34390e1\">At least one field has been modified\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__li_d34391e1_d34392e1_d34393e1\">An occurrence has been added to or removed from the component\n </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__p_d83972e1_d83973e1_d83974e1\">If an error occurs, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> contains a negative value that identifies the exact error.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__topic_d55557e1_d55558e1_d55559e1_d55560e1_d55561e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1184410e185\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__p_d83978e1_d83979e1_d83980e1\">Use in Form components, and in Service and Report components that are not self-contained.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__topic_d55562e1_d55563e1_d55564e1_d55565e1_d55566e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1184410e195\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__p_d83984e1_d83985e1_d83986e1\">Use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span> to test whether any data in the Form has been modified. The value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span> is actually the inclusive logical OR of the values of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> function for all the occurrences in the Form.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfn1665702600415__p_d83987e1_d83988e1_d83989e1\">Statements that affect the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formmod</span> are the same as those that affect <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancemod</span>, and the return values are determined in the same way.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7278340\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7278340\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$formmod (deprecated) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $formmod (deprecated) Return the modification status of data in the current Form component. Note: The $formmod function is deprecated. It has been superseded by $instancemod , which is applicable to all component types. For more information, see $instancemod . $formmod = Expression set | reset $formmod Return Values Table 1. Values returned in $formmod Value Meaning 0 In the following cases: No field has been modified No occurrences have been added or removed No entities are painted on the form 1 In the following cases: At least one field has been modified An occurrence has been added to or removed from the component If an error occurs, $procerror contains a negative value that identifies the exact error. Use Use in Form components, and in Service and Report components that are not self-contained. Description Use $formmod to test whether any data in the Form has been modified. The value of $formmod is actually the inclusive logical OR of the values of the $occmod function for all the occurrences in the Form. Statements that affect the value of $formmod are the same as those that affect $instancemod , and the return values are determined in the same way. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}